.TH "phylink_mii_c22_pcs_config" 9 "phylink_mii_c22_pcs_config" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
phylink_mii_c22_pcs_config \- configure clause 22 PCS
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" phylink_mii_c22_pcs_config
.BI "(struct mdio_device *pcs "  ","
.BI "unsigned int mode "  ","
.BI "phy_interface_t interface "  ","
.BI "const unsigned long *advertising "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "pcs" 12
a pointer to a \fIstruct mdio_device\fP.
.IP "mode" 12
link autonegotiation mode
.IP "interface" 12
the PHY interface mode being configured
.IP "advertising" 12
the ethtool advertisement mask
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Configure a Clause 22 PCS PHY with the appropriate negotiation
parameters for the \fImode\fP, \fIinterface\fP and \fIadvertising\fP parameters.
Returns negative error number on failure, zero if the advertisement
has not changed, or positive if there is a change.
